Description: Log when the DFA evaluates the indPosIndexOffset and
indIndexOffset operand matches for AddP nodes. Shows whether:
(a) The structural match (ADDP_ANY_REGP__CONVI2L_RREGI_ vs ADDP_ANY_REGP_RREGL)
    succeeds or fails for each pattern
(b) The non-negativity predicate (_lo >= 0) passes or fails

Apply to the GENERATED file, not the source:
  build/linux-x86_64-server-fastdebug/hotspot/variant-server/gensrc/adfiles/dfa_x86.cpp

WARNING: This file is regenerated on rebuild. You must re-apply this
patch after each 'make hotspot'. To make it permanent, modify x86.ad
instead (see below).

Usage: Apply, rebuild with 'make CONF=... hotspot JOBS=...'
       Run with -XX:+PrintIdeal -XX:CompileCommand=compileonly,...
       Grep for [dfa-match] in output.

--- a/build/.../gensrc/adfiles/dfa_x86.cpp
+++ b/build/.../gensrc/adfiles/dfa_x86.cpp

Around line 3061 (indPosIndexOffset match), ADD BEFORE the if statement:

    // === LOGGING: indPosIndexOffset match attempt ===
    if (PrintIdeal) {
      bool struct_ok = STATE__VALID_CHILD(_kids[0], _ADDP_ANY_REGP__CONVI2L_RREGI_) &&
                       STATE__VALID_CHILD(_kids[1], IMML32);
      if (struct_ok) {
        bool pred_ok = n->in(2)->in(3)->as_Type()->type()->is_long()->_lo >= 0;
        tty->print("[dfa-match] AddP(%d): indPosIndexOffset structural=YES predicate(%s) _lo=%ld\n",
                   n->_idx, pred_ok ? "PASS" : "FAIL",
                   (long)n->in(2)->in(3)->as_Type()->type()->is_long()->_lo);
      } else {
        tty->print("[dfa-match] AddP(%d): indPosIndexOffset structural=NO"
                   " (kids[0] valid for CONVI2L_RREGI=%d, kids[1] valid for IMML32=%d)\n",
                   n->_idx,
                   STATE__VALID_CHILD(_kids[0], _ADDP_ANY_REGP__CONVI2L_RREGI_),
                   STATE__VALID_CHILD(_kids[1], IMML32));
      }
    }
    // === END LOGGING ===

Around line 3270 (indIndexOffset match), ADD BEFORE the if statement:

    // === LOGGING: indIndexOffset match attempt ===
    if (PrintIdeal) {
      bool struct_ok = STATE__VALID_CHILD(_kids[0], _ADDP_ANY_REGP_RREGL) &&
                       STATE__VALID_CHILD(_kids[1], IMML32);
      if (struct_ok) {
        tty->print("[dfa-match] AddP(%d): indIndexOffset structural=YES (no predicate, takes rRegL)\n",
                   n->_idx);
      }
    }
    // === END LOGGING ===

---

ALTERNATIVE: To make this permanent (survives rebuild), modify x86.ad
at line 5736. Replace the predicate with a logging wrapper. Note: the
ADLC predicate must be a single C++ expression, so use a GNU statement
expression ({...}):

  predicate(({
    bool _result = n->in(2)->in(3)->as_Type()->type()->is_long()->_lo >= 0;
    if (PrintIdeal) {
      tty->print("[ad-predicate] indPosIndexOffset AddP(%d): _lo=%ld → %s\n",
                 n->_idx,
                 (long)n->in(2)->in(3)->as_Type()->type()->is_long()->_lo,
                 _result ? "PASS" : "FAIL");
    }
    _result;
  }));

This GNU extension works with GCC/Clang but is not standard C++.
If the ADLC rejects it, use the dfa_x86.cpp approach above instead.
